Consumer Protection and Technical Regulatory Authority was established on January 1st 2019 by merging the Consumer Protection Board and the Technical Regulatory Authority with the aim of strengthening the capacity of market regulation and safety supervision and the consumer environment.

Our main activities are safety supervision, market regulation and control of compliance with legal obligations in the following areas:
• electronic communications, frequency management and media services;
• rail transport and the implementation of EU structural instruments;
• safety of works and equipment and products with special competence requirements;
• buildings, infrastructure and energy efficiency;
• consumer rights.

In performing our tasks, we offer the following services:
• granting of operating and use rights (industrial, construction and railway safety, electronic and radio communications);
• public oversight (industrial safety, construction, energy efficiency, railway safety, electronic communications and media services, use of radio frequencies, consumer rights);
• consultancy activities;
• consumer dispute resolution.

Our mission is to create a safe and fair living environment.
Our vision is an innovative and responsible living environment for everyone.

